  "text": "Nitroglycerine, which is a pro-drug for nitric oxide (NO), has been known to be able to induce headache in normal volunteers [CITATION_1] and migraine attacks in migraine suffers [CITATION_2] . NO is involved with regulating vasculature diameter S104 Neurol Sci (2013) 34 (Suppl 1):S101-S108",
